x a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n../2755-d60be982/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n../2755-d60be982/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n../2755-d60be982/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n../2755-d60be982/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n../2755-d60be982/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:158:    \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:254:[dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md) per-class\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/architecture.md:209:| `dynamic_access_iterative` | [dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py) | Coverage-driven loop using the dynamic-access report; targets uncovered call sites. |\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/architecture.md:210:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | [optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py](../ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py) | Variant of dynamic-access that primes coverage from source analysis. |\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/architecture.md:247:| `dynamic_access_report` | Parse `dynamic-access-coverage.json`, compute deltas, format prompts. |\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/architecture.md:279:  recovery, dynamic-access iteration, javac/java-run failure prompts).\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:21:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:33:   dynamic-access coverage of already-supported libraries.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:83:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:84:  strategies; see [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md).\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:96:  `dynamic-access-iteration`).\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:125:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:208:For dynamic-access workflows, Forge passes the issue number and configured\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:210:dynamic-access report exceeds a configured class or call chunk limit, the\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:221:- [Dynamic access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) — guided test\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:222:  generation driven by the dynamic-access coverage report.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:231:  final recovery to Codex. Used as the per-class gate in the dynamic-access\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/functional-spec.md:238:  additional tests to improve dynamic-access coverage on an existing library\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:41:> [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:143:where `<class-key>` is a sanitized form of the dynamic-access class the\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:404:| Dynamic-access workflow | [dynamic-access-workflow.md](dynamic-access-workflow.md) |\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:9:  - `run(...)`: runs a single generation attempt. It generates the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to `BasicIterativeStrategy` only if no usable guidance exists at the start, otherwise enters the dynamic-access class iteration immediately and counts success only after metadata generation, retest, `generateLibraryStats`, and a commit for the library iteration succeed.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:10:  - `__init__(...)`: keeps the dynamic strategy config minimal by requiring only the class-specific dynamic-access prompt and dynamic-access-specific iteration limits, while providing internal defaults for the start-of-run basic fallback prompts and fallback iteration limits.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:11:  - `_run_dynamic_access_phase(...)`: uncovered-class iteration using coverage deltas from dynamic-access reports; initializes `exhausted_classes = set()` for the phase, emits targeted prompts per uncovered class, includes the current uncovered dynamic-access call-site list in every prompt, retries `./gradlew test` failures inside a bounded per-class mini-loop by sending the failing output back to the agent, clears agent context after each class attempt sequence, treats the phase as successful once any dynamic-access call site becomes covered, enforces per-class prompt-attempt limits, and fails the generation if the dynamic-access report disappears mid-phase.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:37:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:52:| Output directory | Caller | Absolute path for fallback native-trace metadata. The caller picks a path namespaced per (library, class) for the dynamic-access caller, or per coordinate for non-class-scoped callers — same convention as [native-metadata-exploration.md §4](native-metadata-exploration.md#4-output). On a trace-backed `PASSED`, the gate merges all accepted per-cycle trace dirs into this directory (one `mergeNativeTraceMetadata` invocation). If the JVM-agent metadata path alone passes, this directory may remain empty. |\n../2755-d60be982/forge/docs/native-test-verification.md:220:| `dynamic_access_iterative` per-class loop ([dynamic-access-workflow.md §6.2 / §6.4](dynamic-access-workflow.md)) | After every class with a coverage gain (Resolved or PartialCommit) | `tests/src/<